<TITLE> Patuakhali on alert </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Patuakhali, Nov 14 (bdnews24.com)  Patuakhali river port authorities Wednesday suspended operations of launches and trawlers along inland routes following the brewing of a severe storm in the Bay of Bengal, an official said. Patuakhali Deputy Commissioner Mir Mashiur Alam said the administration had formed two separate committeesone for Golachipa and the other for Kalapara upazilas. People living in coastal areas including Kuakata and Rangabali were asked to move to safety. Nimai Chandra, general secretary of Mahipur Fish Businessmen's Association, said that over 100 trawlers had returned to the coast. Other trawlers were asked to return. Those out of cellphone network could not be informed. bdnews2
